Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 173, 21. Name Damokles. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0116.05.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0899)
